        "timestamp": 1750322023
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I am not saying Lurie is wrong, but that he is misquoted!</p>",
        "id": 524839581,
        "sender_full_name": "Jo√´l Riou",
        "timestamp": 1750322125
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I was more saying that since the author is writing <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"script\">S</mi><mo>‚àó</mo></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathcal{S}_*</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.075em;\">S</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1757em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.075em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mbin mtight\">‚àó</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> for pointed spaces, an answer in Lurie-only framework disregarding the other uses of word \"Space\" was to be expected.<br>\nI guess this is why some people started using the word \"anima\" for Kan complexes/Spaces/Infinity-groupoids...</p>",
        "id": 524840910,
        "sender_full_name": "Robin Carlier",
        "timestamp": 1750322685
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh, but you were referring to using this particular link in the situation of this thread, apologies for the confusion...</p>",
