    {
        "content": "<p>Most parts of this theory are clearly far off, but the mention of the Thom isomorphism is pretty key I think because of how the \"real orientation\" function from Immersion(S‚Åø  √ó ùîª¬π, S‚Åø √ó ùîª¬π) to S‚Å∞ can be used to show invariance of domain.</p>",
